data.description: This charming 3 bedroom, 2 bath home is located in historic Beauregard Town, one of downtown Baton Rouge's most sought-after neighborhoods. Beauregard Town was founded in 1806 and is a Designated National Historic District. This home was constructed in 1904 and features wood flooring, 12 foot ceilings, and decorative plaster crown moldings throughout. This is one of only a handful of homes in Baton Rouge with a basement. The spacious front porch is a great spot for catching up with friends and neighbors, or just taking it easy on a pleasant evening. Each of the two larger bedrooms has it's own en suite full bathroom. The third bedroom would make a great office or media room, as it has doors to both the foyer and living room. Located just a short walk from both the City and Parish Courthouses, this would be a great home or office for an attorney. Don't miss out. Schedule a private showing today.
